timing_enable_aocv_slack_based(25.10)    timing_enable_aocv_slack_based(25.10)

Name
       timing_enable_aocv_slack_based

Syntax
       timing_enable_aocv_slack_based {0 | 1}

       Default: 0

       Enables AOCV analysis using slack-based method.

       When set to true, the software will try to remove excess pessimism from
       the  graph-based  analysis  (GBA)  AOCV stage counts. The paths to end-
       points, which are under the specified slack criteria (default 0.0  ns),
       are  considered  when  computing  stage  counts.  This allows the stage
       counts and subsequent AOCV derates to be aligned with the failing paths
       - and not unnecessarily punished by derates coming from  related  short
       paths that meet timing requirements.

       Note: A true setting is recommended when performing Setup optimizations
       in Innovus - where over pessimism can cause sub-optimal results.

       See timing_aocv_slack_threshold.

       To use this global variable, use the set command.

